headline: Is United Rentals Still a Bargain After 23% Jump in 2025?
summary: Curious whether United Rentals is a bargain right now? You are not alone, as plenty of investors are eyeing this stock for its value potential. United Rentals has jumped 23.0% year-to-date, despite a 10.7% dip in the past month, and is still up a whopping 144.1% over three years. Recent attention has focused on United Rentals as infrastructure investments and rental demand continue to dominate headlines.
